      {
        "question": "Which model should I use for text in images?",
        "answer": "Use GPT Image 2 for any task requiring in-image text. It handles multilingual scripts including Japanese kana, Cyrillic, and Arabic with layout-precise positioning."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I edit existing images with this skill?",
        "answer": "Yes. Use the image-to-image routes. Nano Banana 2 Edit is the default for identity-preserving edits. GPT Image 2 Edit handles multilingual text replacement."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is there a cost to use this skill?",
        "answer": "The RunComfy CLI requires a paid API key. Each model has its own pricing based on resolution, steps, and number of images generated."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I use this skill without internet access?",
        "answer": "No. All image generation requires network access to the RunComfy Model API. The CLI sends requests and polls for results over HTTPS."
      },
